FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,FA spokeswoman for the government body
OL,8,Fsaid: "Born in 1633, in Suffolk, Mary
OL,9,FBeale was one of the first English
OL,10,Fwomen to work as a professional
OL,11,Fartist, an extraordinary achievement
OL,12,Fwhen women were largely excluded from
OL,13,Fartistic training.
OL,26,@pD@GOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,F"Unlike many of her male
OL,8,Fcontemporaries, she succeeded without
OL,9,Ffinancial support from a wealthy
OL,10,Fpatron. She also trained other women
OL,11,Fin painting, and she is sometimes
OL,12,Fcited as the first woman to have
OL,13,Fwritten an instructional text for
OL,14,Fpainting in English.
OL,16,F"Many of Mary Beale's works were
OL,17,Fmisattributed to male artists for
OL,18,Fgenerations, including to Peter Lely,
OL,19,Fand her own son Charles. Her first
OL,20,Fsolo exhibition came only in 1975.
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,F"Recent exhibitions at the Dulwich
OL,8,FPicture Gallery, Tate Britain and
OL,9,FPhilip Mould Gallery have brought
OL,10,Frenewed attention to her achievements.
OL,12,F"Experts continue to discover more of
OL,13,Fher paintings, correcting historical
OL,14,Fmisattributions."
OL,16,FClaudia Kenyatta and Emma Squire, co-
OL,17,Fchief executive's of Historic England,
OL,18,Fsaid: "Mary Beale was ahead of her
OL,19,Ftime.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUvD@QO]zD@GOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,F"Through talent, resilience and
OL,8,Fdetermination, she forged a successful
OL,9,Fcareer in a world that offered women
OL,10,Ffew opportunities, establishing
OL,11,Fherself as one of the first
OL,12,Fprofessional women artists in England.
OL,14,F"Her remarkable body of work and
OL,15,Finfluence continue to resonate today."
OL,17,FBaroness Twycross, Heritage Minister,
OL,18,Fsaid: "It is fitting that a pioneering
OL,19,Fwoman has become the first ever
OL,20,Fseventeenth century figure to be
OL,21,Fhonoured with a national blue plaque.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUwD@fO]zD@GOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,F"Almost 400 years ago, Mary Beale
OL,8,Fproved that pure artistic skill could
OL,9,Fovercome the barriers that made
OL,10,Fbecoming a professional so much more
OL,11,Fdifficult because of her gender.
OL,13,F"Mary perfectly represents how talent
OL,14,Fis everywhere and reminds us of the
OL,15,Fimportance of nurturing those skills
OL,16,Fin all who possess them. This plaque
OL,17,Fwill be a powerful inspiration to
OL,18,Fwomen and girls today."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUzD@WO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778764275
OL,3,CPlaque unveiled at home of first
OL,4,CEnglish women to work as professional
OL,5,Cartist
OL,7,FPhilip Mould, art expert and
OL,8,Fbroadcaster, said: "Set aside, for a
OL,9,Fmoment, Mary Beale's near singularity
OL,10,Fas a woman artist in a male-dominated
OL,11,Fprofession.
OL,13,F"What is most striking is the sheer
OL,14,Findustry of her portrait practice.
OL,15,FAcademics, divines, and a wide swathe
OL,16,Fof the professional middle classes and
OL,17,Fgentry were captured by her brush
OL,18,Fthrough a dynamic family enterprise,
OL,19,Fwith Beale at its centre, her husband
OL,20,Fworking behind the scenes, and her two
OL,21,Fsons helping to complete compositions.
OL,26,@pD@TOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
